### Control Flow

Control flow statements allow you to make decisions in your code.

**If-Else:**
```c
if (age >= 18) {
    printf("Adult");
} else {
    printf("Minor");
}
```

**Switch Statement:**
Used to select one of many code blocks to be executed.
```c
switch(day) {
  case 1:
    printf("Monday");
    break; // Important to stop execution!
  case 2:
    printf("Tuesday");
    break;
  default:
    printf("Weekend");
}
```
